I wanted to sleep in my own bed in Nigeria, wanted to play with my children back home. Abuja, Nigeria
When I travelled to the United States from Nigeria to have my baby in February, Covid-19 wasn’t big news. But weeks later, I knew it was serious when schools in the US began shutting down as infections rose by the hundreds.
I panicked, especially as Nigeria had also recorded its first case, and never ventured outside my host’s house for fear of infecting myself and my baby.



